      { "S": "Prepare the sauce by whisking together 3 tablespoons fish sauce, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 5 tablespoons brown sugar, 2 tablespoons rice vinegar or tamarind paste, 1 tablespoon Sriracha, and 2 tablespoons peanut butter (if using) in a small bowl until smooth. Set aside." },
      { "S": "Cook 8 ounces rice noodles according to package instructions, just until tender — do not overcook as they will continue to soften in the wok. Drain and rinse under cold water to stop cooking. Toss with a small drizzle of oil to prevent sticking." },
      { "S": "Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat until shimmering. Add 3 cloves minced garlic and 1 sliced bell pepper. Stir for 30 seconds, then add 8 ounces protein." },
      { "S": "Cook the protein: For shrimp, cook 1-2 minutes per side until pink and opaque. For chicken, cook 3-4 minutes total, flipping once, until internal temperature reaches 165°F. For tofu, cook 2-3 minutes per side until golden. If using chicken, wash hands and any surfaces that contacted raw chicken with hot soapy water." },
      { "S": "Push everything to one side of the wok. Add remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons oil to the empty side. Pour in 2 beaten eggs and scramble, breaking into small pieces with a spatula as they set (about 30-45 seconds)." },
      { "S": "Add cooked noodles and sauce to the wok. Toss everything together over high heat for 1-2 minutes until noodles are well coated and heated through." },
